<h3 id="anaconda">Anaconda</h3>
<p>There are two versions of Python that you can choose to install and <a href="https://www.anaconda.com/what-is-anaconda/" target="_blank">Anaconda</a> is the easiest way to do it.</p>
<ol>
  <li><a href="https://www.python.org/download/releases/2.7/" target="_blank">Python 2.7</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.python.org/downloads/release/python-360/" target="_blank">Python 3.6</a></li>
</ol>

<p>I prefer to use Python 2.7 because it is more stable than Python 3.6. But if you prefer installing Python 3.6, go ahead and let me know whether you installed all dependencies successfully in the comments.</p>

